headline.print_headline: Business Briefing; Sales of New Homes Soar to Highest Level in 10 Months

snippet: The Commerce Department said on Wednesday that sales last month rose to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 544,000 units, the highest level since February.
abstract: Commerce Dept reports sales of new single-family homes grew significantly in December 2015, rising 10.8 percent to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 544,000 units, highest level in 10 months.
